extendedInfo.description: Free App with Widgets featuring Daily, Weekly and Monthly Horoscopes and Astrology from Jonathan Cainer. (www.cainer.com)Try Jonathan's 'Spookily Accurate' forecasts for yourself and see!Daily updates Mon-Fri, Weekly and Monthly on Weekends.

reviews.title: Wonderful
reviews.comment: Love me some Jonathan Cainer! He is wonderful! And sooo accurate!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Jonathan Cainer App
reviews.comment: Great App with our favourite Jonathan Cainer.  Just one suggestion with the background being black with white text after reading does affect your eyes.  If the background was white and black text or something of the same this would be helpful and would be a 5 Star winner.
reviews.author: James Shutlar

reviews.title: Love this app . . .I helps my being :-)
reviews.comment: When you need inspiration or direction or just to confirm how you are feeling JC never ceases to amaze me on how accurate his readings are unless our unconcious mind makes it fit. Love the app will get it on iphone when I update . .which is soon as its mentioned in the stars :-)
reviews.author: Vikki Spencer

reviews.title: Almost perfect!
reviews.comment: Awesome app, just wish u could set it to automatically open with your sign..instead of having to manually go to it every time u open the app!!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great
reviews.comment: Pleasant and interesting content, I like the personal tone.  Easy to navigate.  Pictures pleasant without being too much.
reviews.author: John Ladd

reviews.title: Download It Anyway
reviews.comment: It doesn\'t matter whether you believe astrology, or not. Cainer\'s earthly wisdom and analogies are well worth reading no matter what sign you are. One can find something of value in every one of Cainer\'s horoscopes.  Accurate, in my opinion. HTC EVO 4G LTE

reviews.title: Please fix this app.
reviews.comment: Love the app, but it uses a lot of background data on my Galaxy Nexus. Even when not in use, it\'s constantly downloading data. It\'s used only 804KB in the foreground, but 1.8MB in the background since yesterday. What is it doing?
